{
  "texts": [
    "BLEU = BP • exp N n=1",
    "w n log p n, here p n represents the N-gram precisions, w n the weight for each N-gram order, and BP the brevity penalty.",
    "As one of the most widely used evaluation metric for machine translation, BLEU however sometimes favors shorter, generic ADs, even when longer and more detailed ADs would be more informative for the target group.",
    "METEOR METEOR (Banerjee and Lavie, 2005) enhances BLEU by incorporating flexible N-gram matching, including paraphrasing, stemming, and synonym recognition.",
    "here F mean is a harmonic mean of matching precision and recall (which is usually weighted 9 times more than precision), and Penalty is a chunk penalty to account for fluency by penalizing scattered word alignments."
  ]
}